The Governor of Rivers State Nyesom Wike on Sunday visited former Deputy National Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP),Chief Olabode George and presenting himself as aspirant for the post of the president of Nigeria in the 2023 general elections, noting that Nigeria required a leader that is focus and determined to make the country better. Governor Wike who came in company of Oyo State Governor Seyi Makinde, Senator Gabriel Suswan and the party’s National Vice Chairman for South West, Soji Adagunodo sought to be given the opportunity to rule the country. He stated that the PDP must win the 2023 general elections, saying what the party needs was to take the power back to the PDP and it does not need to beg to get the power back. While addressing the PDP faithful after a meeting with the leaders of the PDP, Wike said, “I have spoken to the elders and leaders and I hope they will get across to you what I said to them. Most importantly we can’t continue to leave the country the way it is sliding, something has to be done. “Today the requirement of a leader must be focused with capacity, courage and I can tell you I have the courage and nobody to be afraid of and I have the capacity to make things better for this country. “All I have spoken to you the elders to tell you is that they should give me the opportunity. “What  I am going to do is we are going to take back the power, we are not begging, they will be ready and we are ready, the power belongs to us and we must go and take it back,” he said. Responding, Chief Bode George commended members of the party for turning out in large numbers to receive Governor Wike.